{
  "id": "moral_003",
  "version": 1,
  "title": "Everyone Has a Unique Strength",
  "category": "Moral Stories",
  "coverImage": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/JosepAjith/tellora-kids-privacy-policy@main/images/moral_003/cover.webp",
  "ageGroup": "4-12",
  "readingTime": "5 min",
  "language": "en",
  "pages": [
    {
      "page": 1,
      "image": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/JosepAjith/tellora-kids-privacy-policy@main/images/moral_003/1.webp",
      "text": "A mango tree and a coconut tree grew close by."
    },
    {
      "page": 2,
      "image": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/JosepAjith/tellora-kids-privacy-policy@main/images/moral_003/2.webp",
      "text": "A ripe, yellow mango looked at a mature coconut and laughed."
    },
    {
      "page": 3,
      "image": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/JosepAjith/tellora-kids-privacy-policy@main/images/moral_003/3.webp",
      "text": "The coconut asked, \"Why are you laughing at me?\""
    },
    {
      "page": 4,
      "image": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/JosepAjith/tellora-kids-privacy-policy@main/images/moral_003/4.webp",
      "text": "The mango replied, \"See how beautiful I am and how ugly you are!\""
    },
    {
      "page": 5,
      "image": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/JosepAjith/tellora-kids-privacy-policy@main/images/moral_003/5.webp",
      "text": "Suddenly, a parrot came and pecked at the mango. The mango cried."
    },
    {
      "page": 6,
      "image": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/JosepAjith/tellora-kids-privacy-policy@main/images/moral_003/6.webp",
      "text": "Later, during a heavy rainstorm, both the mango and the coconut fell to the ground."
    },
    {
      "page": 7,
      "image": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/JosepAjith/tellora-kids-privacy-policy@main/images/moral_003/7.webp",
      "text": "The mango was bruised, but the coconut was unharmed and smiling."
    },
    {
      "page": 8,
      "image": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/JosepAjith/tellora-kids-privacy-policy@main/images/moral_003/8.webp",
      "text": "Both rolled towards the river."
    },
    {
      "page": 9,
      "image": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/JosepAjith/tellora-kids-privacy-policy@main/images/moral_003/9.webp",
      "text": "The mango drowned in the river, while the coconut floated happily."
    },
    {
      "page": 10,
      "image": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/JosepAjith/tellora-kids-privacy-policy@main/images/moral_003/10.webp",
      "text": "The mango thought, \"We must not laugh at others. Each of us has a unique power.\""
    }
  ],
  "moral": "Never laugh at others. Everyone has unique strengths and qualities that make them special.",
  "isFeatured": true,
  "isPremium": false
}
